grits
------------------------------------------
Virtual Globe library using GTK+ and OpenGL

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libGL1-19.1.6-1
  libGLU-devel-9.0.2-1
  libGLU1-9.0.2-1
  libX11-devel-1.8.10-1
  libX11_6-1.8.10-1
  libcairo2-1.18.4-1
  libgdk_pixbuf2.0_0-2.36.11-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.86.0-1
  libglib2.0_0-2.86.0-1
  libgrits-devel-0.8.1-1bl2
  libgrits5-0.8.1-1bl2
  libgtk2.0-devel-2.24.33-1
  libgtk2.0_0-2.24.33-1
  libsoup2.4-devel-2.60.3-1
  libsoup2.4_1-2.60.3-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.3-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libGL-devel-19.1.6-1
  libGLU-devel-9.0.2-1
  libX11-devel-1.8.10-1
  libcairo-devel-1.18.4-1
  libgdk_pixbuf2.0-devel-2.36.11-1
  libglib2.0-devel-2.86.0-1
  libgtk2.0-devel-2.24.33-1
  libsoup2.4-devel-2.60.3-1
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  http://pileus.org/grits/

Canonical download:
  https://salsa.debian.org/debian-gis-team/grits.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack grits-0.8.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./grits-0.8.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/grits-0.8.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/grits-0.8.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrits5-0.8.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgrits-devel-0.8.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

